The paper discusses the implementation of software citation principles in the scholarly community, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). It also addresses issues related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) in the context of software citation. Additionally, the paper touches on the topic of cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it relates to the persistence and accessibility of software. Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of attributing credit to research software, which could potentially fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
